This paper deals with privacy concerns related to Internet service operators and their use of IPv6 addresses. The paper proposes a new method for anonymizing IPv6 addresses, which is relevant to the field of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves data analysis and aggregation techniques, which could fall under the categories of databases (cs.DB) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses implementation and scalability issues, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
